description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit an enthusiastic speech and language therapist to join the our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This a split post across the pre-school and mainstream schools teams, so would provide an opportunity for the therapist to develop skills in working with a wide range of children in different settings. ( Schools, clinics, and specialist nurseries)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your role would include:&lt;br /&gt;• The assessment and therapy into allocated schools for children with a range of speech, language and communication needs including: language, speech, social communication, selective mutism. &lt;br /&gt;• Working directly with children in groups and individually, as well as offering advice and strategies to school staff and parents. &lt;br /&gt;• Liaising with parents and other professionals&lt;br /&gt;• Providing training to other professionals&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We can offer:&lt;br /&gt;• A team base with other SLTs and multi-disciplinary colleagues &lt;br /&gt;• Regular team meetings&lt;br /&gt;• Access to clinical specialists for second opinions/support&lt;br /&gt;• Admin support&lt;br /&gt;• Opportunities for continuous professional development through a range of learning experiences including opportunities to shadow colleagues&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameFiona WeirJob titlePrincipal Speech and Language TherapistEmail addressfionaweir@nhs.netTelephone number020 8736 7101Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fiona Weir - Principal Speech and Language Therapist on 020 8736 7101&lt;/p&gt;
